# Hands-On Exercise: Smart Contract Security Introduction

## Exercise 1: Analyze Smart Contract

Review this simple Solidity contract for vulnerabilities:

```solidity
contract SimpleBank {
    mapping(address => uint) balances;

    function withdraw(uint amount) public {
        msg.sender.call{value: amount}("");
        balances[msg.sender] -= amount;
    }
}
```

Question: What vulnerability exists? (Hint: reentrancy)

## Exercise 2: Wallet Security Audit

Check your crypto wallet security:
- [ ] Using hardware wallet or secure software wallet?
- [ ] Seed phrase backed up securely offline?
- [ ] Never shared private keys?
- [ ] Verified wallet addresses before sending?
